On 14 =D0=BC=D0=B0=D1=80=D1=82=D0=B0 2009 21:31:59 Maciej Kazulak wrote:
> ioctl(0, SNDCTL_TMR_TIMEBASE or TCGETS, {B38400 opost isig icanon
> echo ...}) =3D 0 ioctl(0, SNDCTL_TMR_TIMEBASE or TCGETS, {B38400 opost
> isig icanon echo ...}) =3D 0 ioctl(0, SNDCTL_TMR_TIMEBASE or TCGETS,
> {B38400 opost isig icanon echo ...}) =3D 0 readlink("/proc/self/fd/0",
> "/dev/ttyS1"..., 4095) =3D 10
> open("/dev/ttyS1", O_RDWR|O_NOCTTY
>
> And it stops there.

Which implies, that

=2D terminal is in -clocal mode
=2D carrier detect signal is not present

There are two issues here

=2D OS seems to lie. In -clocal mode lack of carrier detect should result=20
in HUP signal and no communication should be possible.

=2D should zsh really reopen terminal? If we need additional fd, it could=20
just dup() it?

Interesting, Mandriva RPM has patch that opens tty with O_NONBLOCK;=20
presumably exactly to work around this issue. I am still not convinced=20
that it is the right way; I would really like to understand what happens=20
with tty driver. Could you dump full contents of struct termios *? I=20
believe in Linux it should be something like

strace -e verbose=3Dioctl ...

